# 6. 【K】との出会い

Luka: And Mizuki was the one who sent that message.
Ena: Yeah.
Ena: I was so happy that time...
Ena: Because someone had made a video out of the drawing I'd worked so hard on.
Mizuki: Hehe. That's good to hear. I'm glad I made it.
Ena: After I discovered Kanade's music, I was able to start taking a harder look at my art...
Ena: I also realized then that I could keep drawing.
Ena: After that... We agreed that you should upload that video you made, Mizuki, since you put so much effort into it.
Mizuki: While you hoped that K would see it and like it, right?
Ena: H-Hey, they don't need to hear that part...!
Mizuki: Haha. Sorry. Anyway, I uploaded it right after that.
Mizuki: And about a week later...
Mizuki: K sent me a DM.
Mizuki: Huh...?
Mizuki: Hold up... Is this real?
Mizuki: I guess I can take a peek at it...
Message: <To Amia...>
Message: <My name is K. It's nice to make your acquaintance. I apologize if this is sudden, but I took the liberty of watching the video you posted the other day.>
Message: <And I'd like to tell you that I enjoyed it very much.>
Message: <Again, I know this is sudden, but would it be possible for you to make a music video for the next song? I can't offer much, but I'd like to compensate you for your work.>
Mizuki: ...!
Message: <I'll be looking forward to hearing back from you. Sincerely, K.>
Mizuki: K wants me to make another video...?
Mizuki: Hmm... This could be the real K, but...
Mizuki: <Thank you for your message. This is Amia. Thank you for watching my video. I'm happy to hear that you enjoyed it.>
Mizuki: <And to be personally asked to make another music video... I'm stunned with disbelief. However...>
Mizuki: (This account... It's using the default avatar and has zero followers... I can't help but feel suspicious...)
Mizuki: <I apologize in advance, but I need to be sure of something first. Can you present me with any proof that you are actually K?>
Mizuki: I've seen more than a few people who force others into producing stuff for them like this...
Mizuki: Oh, I got a reply.
[K]: <I appreciate your response.>
[K]: <I'm not sure this will count as proof, but I can send over the demos of the songs I've made in the past.>
Mizuki: Whoa...! I'm being barraged with files!
Mizuki: What if they're viruses...? No, I'm being too paranoid... Let's have a look...
Mizuki: Oh, it's that song... But a rougher version of it... Which means...
Mizuki: That's so cool... You can totally tell it's K even though they're just demos.
Mizuki: (There's no way they'd go this far just to pull a fast one on someone like me.)
Mizuki: (So... This is really them...)
Mizuki: I never expected to be asked by K to make a video like this...
Mizuki: K... I wonder what they're like...
Mizuki: (What kind of personality do you need to have in order to produce songs that feels so dark and painful, but also kind and gentle...?)
Mizuki: (At the same time, my curiosity being the driving factor behind me wanting to work with them probably isn't great...)
Mizuki: (However...)
Mizuki: ...
Mizuki: <I apologize for bringing your identity into question. Thank you for sending me those demos.>
Mizuki: <If possible, I'd like to hear a little more about your proposition...>
[K]: <I understand. Do you happen to have a Nightcord account, Amia...?>
Mizuki: (Nightcord...? I used it a lot back in the day when I was still playing online games.)
Mizuki: <Yes, I do.>
[K]: <Would it be possible for us to talk on there? I believe things will proceed much smoother if we do.>
Mizuki: I get to talk with K...?
Mizuki: <Understood.>
[K]: <Thank you very much. Then, let's talk again later. Preferably tonight at 25:00.>
Mizuki: Huh? That's pretty late...
[K]: <I'd like to have the other person I work with be there as well, and they're generally only free to talk at this time...>
Mizuki: (They work as a team...? I couldn't tell since I didn't notice any credits.)
Mizuki: <Okay, we can talk then.>
[K]: <I appreciate it.>
[K]: <Oh, also... I've already contacted Enanan, so we may all be able to talk to one another.>
Mizuki: (They already got a hold of Enanan...?!)
Mizuki: (That's great. Enanan also said they really like K's songs, so I'm sure they're over the moon about this.)
Mizuki: <Understood. I have no issues with that.>
[K]: <Okay, then we'll talk again on...>
[K]: <Nightcord at 25:00.>
Mizuki: It's time...
Mizuki: Alright, I'll log in...
Mizuki: <Good evening. This is Amia...>
[K]: <Oh, good evening... This is K... Um... Thank you for joining us today.>
Mizuki: <No, thank you as well. You caught me by surprise, but I was also really happy to hear from you...>
[K]: <I see... I'm glad to hear that.>
Mizuki: (So this is K...)
Mizuki: (Based on that voice... She's a girl? Pretty young too. She could be around the same age as me...)
Mizuki: (A teenager? Producing the songs that she does? That's pretty incredible.)
[K]: <Oh... I think Enanan and Yuki are here now... Um, Yuki's the person I mentioned earlier who I work with.>
[Enanan]: <H-Hello...?>
[Yuki]: <Good evening. I apologize for running late.>
Mizuki: <Oh, um...>
[Yuki]: <Oh, where are my manners...? Please allow me to introduce myself. My name is Yuki. I work on creating songs with K.>
[Yuki]: <Actually, I just handle the arranging while K does the actual composing... It's a pleasure to meet both of you.>
[Enanan]: <Oh, um... I-It's my pleasure as well...>
[Enanan]: <I'm E-Enanan... And... It's nice to meet all of you.>
Mizuki: <Oh, Enanan... We've spoken through messages, but this is my first time actually talking to you.>
[Enanan]: <Huh?>
Mizuki: <It's nice to finally meet you. I'm Amia.>
[Enanan]: <A-Amia...?! I didn't realize you were here!>
Mizuki: <Yes, it's me. Thank you for giving me permission to use your art.>
[Enanan]: <Of course...! But actually getting to talk like this feels so strange...>
[Enanan]: <Anyway, I'll set that aside for now... There's something I'd like to ask you, K...>
[Enanan]: <A-Are you really sure about using my art for this...?>
[K]: <What?>
[Enanan]: <It's just... Yes, I was beyond ecstatic when you contacted me about this...>
[Enanan]: <But I took a step back and thought that someone else's art would be more suitable...>
Mizuki: (Oh... She's such an amazing artist, but doesn't have much confidence in herself...)
Mizuki: (How's K gonna respond...? Just trying to comfort her probably isn't the right answer...)
[K]: <No, your art is incredible.>
[K]: <At the very least, I genuinely thought that.>
[Yuki]: <I agree with K on this one...>
[Yuki]: <You could feel this torrent of powerful emotions... And so much sadness... It's clear that you put quite a lot of thought into your piece as you drew it...>
[Enanan]: <Oh... Thank you very much...>
Mizuki: <...>
[K]: <So, I first saw the music video that you two worked on the night before last...>
[K]: <And I was struck by how you'd managed to carefully capture everything we hoping to express through this song.>
[K]: <On top of that... I could feel and understand that powerful urge to shout out loud.>
Mizuki: ...!
Mizuki: (That's the same thing I felt when I saw her illustration...)
Mizuki: (It's like she was shouting, “I can keep going,” or, “I want to keep walking”...)
Mizuki: (And I made my video with that in mind, as well as a few of my feelings sprinkled in...)
Mizuki: (That's really incredible... We all felt the same thing.)
[Yuki]: <Thanks to the video that you two made, Amia, Enanan, our songs have been receiving more views and comments.>
[Yuki]: <It seems like more people have been listening to our songs than ever before, so we greatly appreciate what you've done.>
[Enanan]: <Um, well... That's because your song was so good, but...!>
[Enanan]: <But... I'm really glad that my skills could be of service.>
[K]: <I'd also like to have the songs we make heard by more people...>
[K]: <And I believe that we'll be able to do that if you keep making music videos for us, Enanan, Amia. That's why I decided to ask you to help us...>
Mizuki: <To reach more people...?>
[K]: <Yes...>
Mizuki: (Does that mean she wants to go pro or something...? For a moment there, she got a little intense...)
[K]: <And this is the demo for our next song...>
[K]: <It's still a bit rough, but please listen to it if you like.>
[Enanan]: <Wait, are you sure? This song hasn't been released yet, right?>
[K]: <Yes, that's right. We'd like you to make the music video for it.>
Mizuki: (I wonder what kind of song it...)
Mizuki: ...!
Mizuki: (This song... It's completely different from the other ones! It's so scary and jarring...)
Mizuki: (But there's still that bit of kindness...)
Mizuki: (Her other songs included, K's music always seems to include that kind and gentle feeling somewhere...)
Mizuki: (It's almost like she's trying to reach out to me with her hand...)
[Enanan]: <This is amazing...>
[K]: <As far as design requirements go, I have none. I won't mind what you make as long as you find a way to express what you feel after hearing this song.>
Mizuki: <So, we're free to do what we like...?>
[K]: <Yes.>
Mizuki: (She trusts us this much after just seeing one music video we made...?)
Mizuki: (I'm still having trouble understanding what she's thinking...)
Mizuki: (But...)
[Yuki]: <How do you feel about this, Amia...? It sounded like you were still undecided.>
[Enanan]: <Huh? Is that true?>
Mizuki: <Y-Yes... I thought I should hear more details before coming to a decision.>
Mizuki: <But...>
Mizuki: <After hearing your explanation, as well as this demo, I've decided that I want to do this...>
[K]: <Th-Thank you very much...>
[Yuki]: <This is wonderful news, K. And thank you, Amia. We look forward to working with you.>
[Enanan]: <I'm looking forward to working with you as well, Amia!>
Mizuki: <Likewise. Thank you all very much.>
Mizuki: (There's still a lot that I don't know... But...)
Mizuki: (Right now... I know for sure that I want to do this...)
